cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on automated Facial Emotion Recognition (FER) using machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, to classify emotions in videos. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also explores various methods of fusing features extracted from visual and audio elements, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SD) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of human-machine interactions and the potential impact on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
